 in the early twentieth century.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aThis eBook is made available Open Access under a CC BY-NC-ND 4.0 license: uhttps://creativecommons.org/licenses/by-nc-nd/4.0 uhttps://www.degruyter.com/dg/page/open-access-policy  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 17. Dez 2021) 0aAuthorshipxHistoryyTo 1500. 0aCivilization, Medieval. 0aLiterature, MedievalxHistory and criticismxTheory, etc. 0aPhilosophy, Medieval. 4aKultur des Mittelalters. 4aLiteratur des Mittelalters. 4aPerformativität. 7aLITERARY CRITICISM / Medieval.2bisacsh  aMedieval Culture.  aMedieval Literature.  aPerformative.1 aFlorence, Melanie, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aGragnolati, Manuele, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aGragnolati, Manuele, eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt1 aLampart, Fabian, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aMacRobert, C. M., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aMatthews, Alastair, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aOtter, Monika, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aRees, Owen, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aSoutherden, Francesca, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aSuerbaum, Almut, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aSuerbaum, Almut, eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt1 aSutherland, Annie, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aThompson, Benjamin, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertDGBA Backlist Complete English Language 2000-2014 PART1z978311023857008iTitle is part of eBook packag